{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "api-gateway-comic-sans",
		"name": "API Gateway — Comic Sans",
		"description": "# API Gateway Documentation\n\n## Overview\nThe **api-gateway** is a Go microservice (port **8080**) that acts as the single entry point for the React frontend. It validates JWTs on protected routes and proxies requests to internal microservices, injecting `X-User-Id`, `X-Username`, and `X-Internal` headers.\n\n## Architecture\n```\nFrontend → API Gateway → Internal Microservices\n```\n\n## Route Mapping\n| Gateway Path | Target Service | JWT Required |\n|---|---|---|\n| POST /api/auth/* | auth-service (3001) | No |\n| /api/users/* | user-service (3002) | Yes |\n| /api/catalog/* | catalog-service (3003) | Yes |\n| /api/customers/* | customer-service (3004) | Yes |\n| /api/sales/* | sales-service (3005) | Yes |\n| /api/reports/* | report-service (3006) | Yes |\n\n## Standard Response Envelope\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true | false,\n  \"data\": { ... } | null,\n  \"error\": null | \"Descriptive error message\"\n}\n```\n\n## Usage\n1. First, call **Login** to obtain a JWT token (auto-saved to `auth_token` variable)\n2. Then use any protected endpoint — the token is automatically included via `Bearer {{auth_token}}`",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "base_url",
			"value": "http://localhost:8080",
			"type": "string",
			"description": "Base URL of the API Gateway"
		},
		{
			"key": "auth_token",
			"value": "",
			"type": "string",
			"description": "JWT token — auto-populated by the Login request"
		}
	],
